[{"id":"FT561729","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"Which of the following best represents a possible distribution of the ions at temperature <em>T</em><sub>1</sub>?","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n<img alt=\"The figure shows a rectangle with 10 circles scattered throughout. 5 circles contain a positive sign and 5 circles contain a negative sign.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/bfe32fc81c4f32e7a662db58cee1fa0f/original.png\">\n<p>A very hot gas composed of equal numbers of positive and negative ions is in a closed, thermally insulated container and is in thermal equilibrium at temperature <em>T</em><sub>0</sub>. The figure above represents the initial distribution of the ions. A strong uniform electric field directed toward the bottom of the page is now created in and around the container, and the gas is allowed to reach a new thermal equilibrium at temperature <em>T</em><sub>1</sub>.</p>"}],"choicesHtml":["<img alt=\"Option A shows 5 circles arranged in a scattered row near the top of the rectangle and 5 circles arranged in a scattered row near the bottom of the rectangle. The top row is arranged from left to right as positive, negative, positive, positive, positive, and negative. The bottom row is arranged from left to right as positive, negative, negative, negative, and positive. \" height=\"167\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/603f4a7f64c5a107d72141d4e85a65e6/original.png\" width=\"130\">","<img alt=\"Option B shows 3 circles containing positive signs arranged in a row along the very top of the rectangle and 2 circles containing negative signs arranged in a row just below, and in between, the 3 circles along the very top. 3 circles containing negative signs are arranged in a row along the very bottom of the rectangle and 2 circles containing positive signs are arranged in a row just above, and in between, the 3 circles along the very bottom.\" height=\"165\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/95fdd81c685d9d112d367729afabe0b8/original.png\" width=\"130\">","<img alt=\"Option C shows 5 circles containing negative signs arranged within the top half of the rectangle in a scattered pattern and 5 circles containing positive signs arranged within the bottom half of the rectangle in a scattered pattern.\" height=\"164\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/29ac08772a367615ef4c26c7d7153528/original.png\" width=\"130\">","<img alt=\"Option D shows 5 circles containing positive signs arranged within the top half of the rectangle in a scattered pattern and 5 circles containing negative signs arranged within the bottom half of the rectangle in a scattered pattern.\" height=\"170\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/7c8c3426839c60ef77b008c309247418/original.png\" width=\"130\">"],"answer":1}]